* identity_persistence_regression.dts
* Identity/RBAC DBF persistence round-trip proof (AIF-045 2b-ii, APH-5).
*
* Saves the seeded identity catalog to DBF, reloads it, and confirms the reloaded
* store is structurally identical (row counts), preserves user id/key/profile, and
* resolves every member x permission to the same authorize() verdict. This is the
* runtime half of APH-5 self-hosting: x64base -> reload -> x64base, identity intact.
*
* Expected (grep between BEGIN/END):
*   USER SAVE: wrote identity catalog to ...
*   USER VERIFY: PASS  (dir=..., decisions N/N agree)
*
* Writes only DBF tables under data/metadata/identity(_verify); mutates no fixture.
*
* Run:  REGRESSION RUN IDENTITY_PERSIST
*   or: DOTSCRIPT dottalkpp/data/scripts/dotscript/identity_persistence_regression.dts

SET ECHO OFF
STOP_ON_ERROR OFF

FORMULA "IDENTITY-PERSIST-REGRESSION-BEGIN"
FORMULA "save the seeded identity catalog to DBF:"
USER SAVE
FORMULA "reload it (report-only):"
USER LOAD
FORMULA "APH-5 round-trip proof (expect PASS, all decisions agree):"
USER VERIFY
FORMULA "IDENTITY-PERSIST-REGRESSION-END"
